{"arkId":"cl010421777","url":"https:\/\/collections.louvre.fr\/ark:\/53355\/cl010421777","modified ":"2025-08-25","title":"Coupe sur pied : Neptune","titleComplement":"","denominationTitle":[{"type":"Titre","value":"Coupe sur pied : Neptune"}],"displayDateCreated":"Date de cr\u00e9ation\/fabrication : 1550 - 1575","currentLocation":"Richelieu, [OArt] Salle 507 - Galerie des Chasses de Maximilien, Vitrine 10, Verticale B","room":"Salle 507, Aile Aile Richelieu, Niveau 1","isMuseesNationauxRecuperation":false,"dateCreated":[{"startYear":1550,"endYear":1575,"imprecision":"","text":"3e quart du XVIe si\u00e8cle","type":"Date de cr\u00e9ation\/fabrication","doubt":""}],"creator":[{"label":"P\u00e9nicaud, Jean III","attributionLevel":"Attribution actuelle","linkType":"Attribu\u00e9 \u00e0","creatorRole":"Emailleur","authenticationType":"","doubt":"","attributedBy":"","attributedYear":"","wikidata":"Q18508364"},{"label":"Raimondi, Marcantonio","attributionLevel":"Attribution actuelle","linkType":"D\u0027apr\u00e8s","dates":[{"date":"Vers 1480","place":"Sant\u0027Andrea in Argine\/Bologne","type":"date de naissance"},{"date":"vers 1530","place":"Bologne","type":"date de mort"}],"creatorRole":"Graveur","authenticationType":"","doubt":"","attributedBy":"","attributedYear":"","wikidata":"Q728375"}],"objectNumber":[{"value":"OA 12918","type":"Num\u00e9ro principal"}],"collection":"D\u00e9partement des Objets d\u0027art du Moyen Age, de la Renaissance et des temps modernes","printsDrawingsEntity":"","printsDrawingsCollection":"","objectType":"coupe \u00e0 boire = tazza ; coupe ; \u00e9mail","originalObject":"","printState":"","description":"Coupe en \u00e9mail peint en grisaille avec rehauts de chair et d\u0027or au fond en creux repr\u00e9sentant Neptune. Debout sur une conque tir\u00e9e par quatre chevaux marins, le dieu de la mer est nu, les cheveux et la barbe rejet\u00e9s vers l\u0027arri\u00e8re, tenant un trident dans la main droite; au-dessus de la sc\u00e8ne, deux t\u00eates d\u0027enfant symbolisant les vents \u00e9mergent de nu\u00e9es; bord \u00e0 d\u00e9cor des douze signes du zodiaque. Ext\u00e9rieur de la coupe orn\u00e9e de quatre termes f\u00e9minins reli\u00e9s par des rubans, cartouches, cuirasse, troph\u00e9es, lampes de sanctuaire, chim\u00e8res ail\u00e9es, noeuds et rubans. Divers personnages nus sur le pied dont une femme allong\u00e9e attaqu\u00e9e par un insecte et une ch\u00e8vre ; frise d\u0027entrelacs en bordure. Pied XIXe (?)","inscriptions":"Inscription : \r ; deux signes ou chiffres grav\u00e9s dans l\u0027\u00e9mail (4 et 9 ?) (au revers du pied)","namesAndTitles":"","onomastics":"","dimension":[{"type":"Diam\u00e8tre","value":"18,4","displayDimension":"18,4 cm","unit":"cm","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":1,"note":""},{"type":"Hauteur","value":"11","displayDimension":"11 cm","unit":"cm","anteriorPrecision":"","posteriorPrecision":"","tri":1,"note":""}],"shape":"","materialsAndTechniques":"Technique : \u00e9mail peint (techniques m\u00e9tal-\u003E\u00e9maill\u00e9 = \u00e9maillage = \u00e9mail = \u00e9maux) (en grisaille avec rehauts de chair et d\u0027or)","placeOfCreation":"Limoges (Limousin-\u003EHaute-Vienne = Haute Vienne)","dateOfDiscovery":"","placeOfDiscovery":"","provenance":"","historicalContext":[],"objectHistory":"Collection sir Andrew Fountaine, 1676-1753 ; vente Fountaine Collection, Londres, Christie\u0027s, 16 juin 1884, lot 129 (alors avec un couvercle repr\u00e9sentant le triomphe d\u0027un empereur) ; exposition : \u0022Paris et Catherine de M\u00e9dicis\u0022, Paris, mairie du 1er arrondissement, juillet-ao\u00fbt 1989 (non illustr\u00e9e) ; vente Pierre Berg\u00e9 et Associ\u00e9s, Paris, Drouot, 29 novembre 2017, lot 69","jabachInventory":"","napoleonInventory":"","previousOwner":[{"value":"Fountaine, Andrew","note":"","role":", Collectionneur"}],"acquisitionDetails":[{"mode":"achat par pr\u00e9emption en vente publique","doubt":"","dates":[{"type":"date de comit\u